+---
+title: "*.rb-only gemspec glob silently drops runtime shell scripts"
+date: 2026-07-11
+category: architecture-patterns
+module: Hive::ClaudeLauncher
+problem_type: packaging_gotcha
+component: gem_packaging
+severity: high
+tags: [packaging, gemspec, tmux, claude, ready-detector]
+applies_when:
+  - "spec.files enumerates lib with a *.rb glob but the runtime execs non-.rb assets"
+  - "A code path shells out to a file shipped under lib/ (bash wrapper, template, data file)"
+  - "A defect only reproduces on a clean gem install, not in a source checkout"
+---
+
+# `*.rb`-only gemspec glob silently drops runtime shell scripts
+
+## Problem
+
+`hive.gemspec` built `spec.files` from an explicit allowlist that used
+`lib/**/*.rb`. `Hive::ClaudeLauncher#wrapper_command` execs
+`lib/hive/scripts/interactive_claude_wrapper.sh`, and
+`Hive::StopHookInstaller` references `lib/hive/scripts/stop_hook.sh` — neither
+is a `.rb`, so **neither shipped in the built gem**.
+
+The failure is invisible in a source checkout (the files are on disk) and only
+reproduces on a clean gem install: `bash <missing-file>` exits instantly, the
+tmux session dies before Hive can inspect the pane, and `hive run` surfaces
+`claude_launch_failed` / "can't find pane".
+
+## Fix
+
+Add a scripts-specific glob rather than broadening `lib/**/*` (which would
+sweep in unrelated non-`.rb` files):
+
+```ruby
+spec.files = Dir[
+  # ...
+  "lib/**/*.rb",
+  "lib/hive/scripts/**/*.sh",
+  # ...
+]
+```
+
+## Guard (the durable lesson)
+
+A `spec.files.include?("...")` assertion pins the two known scripts but rots
+when a new script is added. Pair it with two stronger guards:
+
+- **Enumeration-driven:** scan `lib/**/*.rb` for `scripts/\S+\.sh` string
+  literals, resolve each to its path, and assert every one is packaged. New
+  scripts are covered automatically. Also assert the enumeration is non-empty,
+  so a broken regex cannot pass vacuously.
+- **Built-artifact:** `Gem::Package.build(spec)` in a temp dir, then read the
+  packaged file list back via `Gem::Package.new(path).spec.files`. This catches
+  a `spec.files` entry that fails to match any file on disk — the class of bug
+  a plain `spec.files` string check cannot. Gate behind an env flag
+  (`HIVE_GEM_BUILD_TEST=1`) if build cost matters for the default unit run.
+
+Prove the guard has teeth: it must fail on the pre-fix gemspec and pass after.
+
+## Generalization
+
+Any allowlist-style `spec.files` that enumerates by extension will drop runtime
+assets of other extensions the moment a code path starts execing/reading them.
+When code shells out to or reads a file shipped under `lib/`, add a packaging
+guard that builds the real artifact — not just a `spec.files` membership check.
