+---
+timestamp: 2026-07-11T00:00:00Z
+title: Fix Claude tmux packaging + version-tolerant ready detector
+---
+
+- Two coupled defects broke `hive run` in Claude tmux mode on a clean
+  `hive-cli` install with Claude Code 2.1.179; both fixed and pinned by tests.
+  See new [[claude-tmux-launcher]].
+- **Packaging.** `hive.gemspec` `spec.files` used `lib/**/*.rb`, which excludes
+  the `*.sh` wrappers under `lib/hive/scripts/`
+  (`interactive_claude_wrapper.sh`, `stop_hook.sh`). A clean install ran
+  `bash <missing-file>`; the tmux session died before inspection and the launch
+  surfaced as `claude_launch_failed`. Added `lib/hive/scripts/**/*.sh` to
+  `spec.files`. Guard in `test/unit/gemspec_test.rb`: spec.files checks for both
+  known scripts, an enumeration-driven scan of `lib/**/*.rb` for `scripts/*.sh`
+  literals asserting each is packaged (non-empty guarded), and a built-gem check
+  behind `HIVE_GEM_BUILD_TEST=1` that reads the real `.gem` file list.
+- **Detector.** Claude Code 2.1.179 renders a boxed prompt
+  (`separator / caret / separator / footer`) with the caret as `❯` + NBSP
+  (U+00A0). `CLAUDE_READY_PROMPT_LINE` / `CLAUDE_MENU_OPTION_LINE` now accept
+  ASCII whitespace, NBSP, and `\p{Zs}`; `CLAUDE_PROMPT_CONTEXT_LINES` raised
+  4 → 12; the fixed 2-line tail scan (`CLAUDE_PROMPT_TAIL_LINES`, retired) is
+  replaced by a chrome-below-caret rule (`CLAUDE_BOX_SEPARATOR_LINE`,
+  `CLAUDE_PROMPT_CHROME_MARKERS`) so the caret is accepted when every non-blank
+  line below it is a box separator or hint/footer line. Negative guards
+  (trust/permission/banner) and menu-option rejection unchanged.
+- Regression coverage: inline NBSP test + committed fixture
+  `test/fixtures/panes/claude_ready_2_1_179.txt`, plus live permission/trust
+  box-layout rejections. All prior detector tests pass unchanged.
+- Out of scope, documented only: daemon/systemd binary drift
+  (`/usr/bin/hive` vs `~/.local/bin/hive`) as an end-to-end validation caveat;
+  publishing the `0.3.3` gem patch is a separate release step. See [[gaps]].
